eNCA's Siphamandla Goge has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Possible corruption with funds meant for the floods in KZN has been in the spotlight since the disaster. President Cyril Ramaphosa says it is shameful that the main concern of the public is potential misappropriation and waste of funds. READ: KZN Floods | Ramaphosa: SA is in mourning once again Ramaphosa addressed both the National Assembly and the National Council of Provinces earlier. He says several measures have been taken to strengthen oversight and accountability. Watch the video above for more details.